changing conventions in several components is not an easy task:
* it would break a lot of tests (making commits rolled back, heh?)
* would create a bigger difference with standard approaches, make our 'upstreamable' patches larger
* would make the documentation larger (anyone willing to document new ABI? I doubt so..)


The whole thing is a cleanup/beautification step, we have more urgent things to do.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-11-01T17:57:19.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-11-01T17:57:19.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 3 by pa...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1131#c3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1131/comments/full/3" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>